<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-108-298 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 970 138</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  July 8 1991 v37 n1868 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sequent exiting OEM business? (Sequent Computer Systems Inc.;andO;original equipment manufacturer)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lapedus, Mark.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Sequent Computer Systems Inc may be moving out of the OEM businessand may eventually sell all of its computers directly toend-users.andP;  The company has ended its OEM deals withSiemens/Nixdorf and MAI Basic Four.andP;  The company originallyannounced that it was leaving the OEM business entirely, but thenqualified its statement by saying that its OEM relationship withUnisys Corp would continue.andP;  Despite these assurances, observersfeel that the Unisys relationship could also dissolve.andO;Unisys-related sales volume is rapidly declining, and Sequent PresScott Gibson is not confident that this trend will reverse itself.andO;Sequent also announced that it would institute its first layoffs,a seven to nine percent workforce reduction that would affectbetween 114 and 153 employees.andP;  Sequent's problems have put itinto the red for its 1st qtr ended Mar 30, 1991, with a loss of$6.96 million on sales of $47.9 million.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sequent Computer Systems Inc. (Planning).andO;Ticker:    SQNT.andO;Topic:     OEMsBusiness PlanningDirect MarketingFirst QuarterLosses.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>